Green Trolley Criterium
description: The Five Star Waste Vegetable Oil Cycling team is dedicated the use and awareness of waste vegetable oil as an alternative fuel.  The team practice what they preach, as the team van and the team owners car run on alternative fuels.  As part of their mission, the team will be holding the Green Trolley Criterium in your neighborhood on June 28th 2008.  The primary purpose of this bicycle race is to further raise awareness of the viability of waster vegetable oils and other alternative fuels.
course: This is the same course as the Red Trolley Classic.  Located in the heart of the Sorrento Valley Business Park, the Top Gun,   Course is a fast .6 mile four corner course. notes: The 2007 Carrera drew thousands of spectators, surpassing the all previous years\\\\\\\' turnouts and setting records in attendance for a single-day participatory sporting event in Northern California. San Francisco Twilight Criterium
description: On September 13th, the speed and adrenaline of professional cycling returns to the streets of San Francisco.  Prepare yourself for the pageantry of the criterium style of racing -- short, fast, urban and gritty. Absorb the romanticism of a twilight race -- part fading sun, part Big City Lights. This isnt cycling you watch. This is cycling you feel.
course: The 1-km SFT course runs clockwise on Union, Fillmore, Greenwich and Buchanan.  The high speed action of night time criterium racing is unparalleled in the world of spectator appeal and action sports.
registration: Invite Only:  Pro Teams contact: proteams@projectsport.com.
notes: Join us for San Franciscos first evening themed sporting event as we transform Union Street into a showcase of professional cycling.  Race fans will see the top cyclists in America compete for thousands of dollars under the lights of Union Street and on one of the country\\\\\\\'s fastest, most exciting race courses.
